This is a good spot for some authentic Dominican food. The food is delicious; that's about the best thing about this restaurant; the rest is pretty average. The prices is what one would expect in this party of the City. The layout of the place is not very conducive to eating in, although the place is not small. However, the front tables are right next to the people ordering, (heavy traffic area), and you don't want to seat in the back, next to the kitchen.... Also, due to the high traffic, the staff are unwilling, or unable to really give personalized care to their customers....

They get 2 stars because the food was good, but if you have limited time DO NOT ORDER FROM HERE!  They were almost 40 minutes late with my order and did not even bother to call to notify.  My lunch hour was over by the time they showed up, so I was barely able to eat.  When the delivery man shows up he calls, and blurts out "DELIVERY".  I was not about to go downstairs to get my food after that long wait and especially since my lunch hour was officially over.  So I pointed out to him that, as per my order, I am in room number 203.  He hangs up and shows up to deliver the food without any apology for the delay.  I do not think I will ever order from this place again.  There is a lot of room for improvement in their customer service quality.

Avoid this place!!! I paid $10.00 for beef over yellow rice with beans. The rice and beef had so much salt and sazon on them that my meal was practically inedible. Since the beans were so watery, I was able to dilute some of the salt, when I poured it over the rice. Regardless, my meal was absolutely HORRIBLE!!! Do not waste your money here. Go to Key Food, right up the block. Near the deli counter, you can get a tray of pork or beef, with rice and beans for $5.00 or a whole rotisserie chicken for $8.00.
Delicious food and fast service  !

Beware when ordering from here, they have a hard time keeping track of orders. They forgot about my order and when I called in to ask about it as I had waited over an hour, I could hear her ask someone in the back if it had gone out already. Then there was commotion where a lot of talk went on, I assume they were trying to figure out where my order was and what to tell me. Then they told me that they were out of the items I wanted (apparently both items are out when she originally thought the order was already completed. I had also told her what my order was at the beginning so wouldn't she know if those items were out of stock?) She then said they tried to call me, which is a complete lie because my phone was near me at all times and I received no calls. If she couldn't contact me, she could've also contacted seamless since I had ordered from the app. They didn't want to complete the order because it was already closing time at this point. She refused to cancel the order from her end, so I had to call seamless to do it myself.
